~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~
Please note about WOOD products:

• It is natural for wood products to have natural scar knots, cracks, mineral lines, blackish areas, uneven pattern, grainy wood color and other natural flaws, so this cannot be classified as a problem in quality.

• Each piece has its individual differences, no two are exactly the same size/colour/texture etc.

How to maintain wood items:

• Exposure to conditions eg. flooding, heating, air conditioning, high-temperature/low-humidity conditions may result in deformation, cracking, mildew.

• Wipe dry immediately after use with a dry cloth, place in a cool ventilated place.

• In a dry environment, you may need to apply some vegetable oil to protect it from cracking.

• Recommended: wash with salt water after 1st use and dry naturally.

• Do not use hot/boiling water as it will destroy the timber structure and shorten its lifespan.

• After cleaning, the surface of wood products may feel a little rough, which is a normal phenomenon. However along with the increase in frequency of use, it will eventually smoothen.

• To maintain beauty/durability over time, apply olive oil and leave to soak for 12 hours so it is absorbed into the wood.
